title: Kyle Busch holds off Kenseth for XFINITY win at Kansas
text:
Kyle Busch holds off Kenseth for XFINITY win at Kansas FOXSports 1 hr ago Â© Getty Images KANSAS CITY, KS - OCTOBER 17: Kyle Busch, driver of the #54 Monster Energy Toyota, leads a pack of cars during the NASCAR XFINITY Series Kansas Lottery 300 at Kansas Speedway on October 17, 2015 in Kansas City, Kansas. (Photo by Jerry Markland/Getty Images)
Kyle Busch held off fellow Sprint Cup veteran Matt Kenseth and the rest of the field to win the Kansas Lottery 300 XFINITY Series race at Kansas Speedway on Saturday.
AdChoices It was Busch's 75th career win in the series.
Kenseth finished second, followed by Daniel Suarez, Ty Dillon and Regan Smith.
Series points leader Chris Buescher overcame a speeding penalty, as did Busch, en route to a respectable sixth-place finish that helped him maintain a healthy lead in the standings.
